text: Legislative elections were held in Israel on 23 March 2021 to elect the 120 members of the 24th Knesset. It was the fourth election in two years. The 24th Knesset was sworn in on 6 April 2021. Thirteen parties/alliances got seats. Winner was HaLikud of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. They got 30 seats. Second was Yesh Atid of Yair Lapid. They got 17 seats. Netanyahu tried unsuccessfully to form a sixth government. Yair Lapid and Naftali Bennett (HaYamin HeHadash) did succeed and formed the Bennett-Lapid Government. ==References== Category:March 2021 events Category:2021 in Israel Category:2021 elections in Asia Category:Knesset
title: 2021 Israeli legislative election
